HOW TO OPEN JAR FILE:

1. Extract zip file to desktop
2. Search and run cmd(windows) or terminal(unix/mac)
3. Change directory to desktop or the file location of the extracted file
4. Change directory to the file folder location. Ex: cd users\**(userprofilehere)***\desktop\NetBeans\RBTreesMain\dist
5. In the command line, type in "java -jar RedBlackTrees.jar"
6. If the file cannot be accessed, make sure you're in the same directory as the file.
7. Once the jar file has been executed, choose an option by typing in any corresponding number string
8. Type -1 to terminate the program
